summary: An ordinance accepting a deed of conveyance from Oliver W. Campbell, and wife, to the City of Seattle, dated the 16th day of March, 1920, quit-claiming all right, title and interest to a certain water piping system located in the Southeast quarter of Section thirty-four (34) and in the Southwest quarter of Section thirty-five (35), all in Township twenty-three (23) North, Range eight (8) East, W.M.
